* Write lock is an exclusive lock
* Read lock is a shared lock.
* If you have a shared lock on a row, you can't get an exclusive lock on it. Similarly when you hold
 exclusive lock you can't get a shared lock.
  + But you can get a shared lock if the object has already a shared lock on it.

* Reference:
  - https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11837428/whats-the-difference-between-an-exclusive-lock-and-a-shared-lock
  - http://dev.cs.ovgu.de/db/sybase9/help/dbugen9/00000154.htm